Hello beautiful friends! 

Your mind is naturally wired to focus on what could go wrong — it’s the negativity bias at work. But what if you could reprogram your Reticular Activating System (RAS) to see opportunity instead of fear?

 Remember:

Your unconscious mind doesn’t see reality; it sees what you imagine.
Life isn’t happening to you; it’s happening through you.
When you take responsibility, you unlock true power.
Your life is a mirror of your mind. Shift your focus, and watch your world transform.

 What are you focused on today?

Amit Singh
posts.content:
One glitch in the matrix, and the entire Airport x DigiYatra experience falls apart!
Here is what happened:

I flew Delhi-Mumbai (delayed due to fog) and back to Delhi(delayed by 3 hours).

The good part was Air India informed in advance the flight is delayed so I arrived at the airport at 10pm, post the orignal departure time, and here is how things got interesting:

 DigiYatra didn’t let me in
 It took some convincing to convince security officer to let me in
 Automatic gates didn’t let me in, asked me to get boarding pass stamped
 Lot of concision at the Air India counters about a regular delay procedure
Finally got in

It’s not a complaint post but this incident made me think hard; how small glitches in any user flow can kill the entire experience.

comments.commentText: Seriously! This is sad, even the smallest things can cause a line of glitches.
